{
  "texts": [
    "Choosing Sequence Length/Reference Model Popular implementations of DPO (Tunstall et al., 2023a,b) use a sequence length of 1024, and a reference model π ref = π SFT.",
    "However, many recent work differs in this setting: using either a longer sequence length (Meng et al., 2024), or a different reference model (Rafailov et al., 2023; Gorbatovski et al., 2024).",
    "We compare these configurations by training Gemma-2b on a 10k randomly sampled subset from the mixture dataset and evaluating on OpenLLM and Arena-Hard-Auto*.",
    "Specially, we measure the impact of 1) using a longer sequence length of 2048, and 2) using different reference models proposed by prior work.",
    "The latter includes using π SFT after further SFT on all chosen responses in the 10k subset (denoted as π ref =SFT chosen); π SFT after additional DPO training on the 10k subset (denoted as π ref =DPO); and using a stronger model such as LLaMA-3-8b (denoted as"
  ]
}